The `try { contradiction }` will try to find an immediate contradiction in the assumptions.

The `try { simp_all [Fin.ext_iff] }` will try to simplify the equality of `Fin 2` expressions. `Fin.ext_iff` states that two functions are equal if they are equal on all inputs.

The `try { omega }` will try to solve the goals using the omega solver, which is good for linear arithmetic.

This approach is feasible because there are only finitely many triples to check. The Lean 4 proof will automatically check all possibilities and find a contradiction in each case.

